curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/6512' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3758", "table_name": "PIN DESCRIPTION", "content": "PIN DESCRIPTION  PIN  NAME  I/O  FUNCTION  1  FB  I  Feedback Input for Current. Connect the sense resistor from FB to GND.  2  STROBE  I  Strobe Signal Input Pin. STROBE synchronizes the flash pulse to the image capture.  Generally, this signal is directly generated from the image sensor.  3  GND  O  Ground Pin.  4  SW  I  Boost Switching Node. The device monitors the output voltage on this pin for LED  open protection. Connect an inductor between the VIN and SW pins.  5  CTRL  I  Boost Regulator Control Pin. It is used for enable control and PWM dimming control.  6  VIN  I  Input Supply Pin.   Exposed Pad  GND  —  Exposed Pad. It should be soldered to the analog ground plane. If possible, use  thermal via connection to ground plane for enhanced power dissipation.    "}'
